reviewText:
The BEST MOVIE ever achieved in simulating what a Dream is and/or could be.

(They haven't done anything like it before, Nor will they ever do anything like it again.)

It gave an Unforgettable memory. Long Live DREAMS THAT MONEY CAN BUY.
This movie was referenced in a book. It was praised. It was a big disappointment. It was just poor: poor acting, poor writing, poor execution.

I rate this for its historical reputation among surrealists and dadaists, but I am being irresponsible.  I've never seen it!  But I wanted to place this review to say if anyone has come here looking for this "unavailable" film, try the website of The Real Tuesday Weld, which seems to have it for order (Weld is a fun musician who recorded an alternative soundtrack for this film.
